description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you committed to delivering excellence in patient care and would like to work for an organization that values its staff and patients? Hadley Wood operating theatres have vacancies for Band 6 theatre practitioners. The successful candidates will need to be adaptable to change, be passionate and motivated about patient care and be committed to delivering a high standard of quality care to our patients within a busy Day surgery environment. Appropriate experience is essential for Band 6 applicants but we are happy to appoint people who are looking to expand their knowledge and skills within our different specialties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hadley Wood Hospital in Barnet is part of the expansion of Private Patient Unit (PPU) and offers patients a wide range of services independently as well as being an integral part of PPU. Hadley Wood Hospital has recently undergone a major refurbishment and now hosts an MRI, CT, Imaging and 2 fully equipped theatres and Endoscopy Suite as well as 2 Day Surgery wards and outpatient facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic opportunity to join the Hadley Wood senior nursing team and lead the theatre teams that are continuing to grow and deliver the highest standards of patient care. We require a dynamic, enthusiastic and well-organised individual to provide clinical, management and professional leadership for the expanding services within Hadley Wood Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate is required to be able demonstrate the Trust values, the responsibilities of the job description and person specification, and previous experience within private health care is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’d love for you to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lolita Ying&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Theatre Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Lolita.ying@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
